In @tomhayes' playful CSS framework, every class name is replaced with an emoji, breaking traditional naming conventions. The framework leverages a PostCSS workflow for processing, allowing developers to use emoji-based class names in their stylesheets while maintaining standard CSS output. Example snippet:
css
/* Traditional */
.button { background: blue; }

/* Emoji-based */
.🔵 { background: blue; }
